author: Urnetta Reid
text: The officials who manage the Caribbean Examination Council, are a law unto themselves. It seems like they are answerable to no one. At no time they've ever taken the students plight, into consideration. All of them should be fired.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Like Bradley Stewart, I agree that it would be a mistake and a joke , to appoint Paul Hall, as the national coach for the Reggae Boys.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: A Jamaican man came first in the cycling race, held in Western Jamaica today, but was disqualified because of cheating, and the American who was second became the winner instead. What's wrong with some of these Jamaicans?

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Oh my Chelsea! What went wrong today?

author: Urnetta Reid
text: The two best teams in the competition are in the final. My bet is on St. Jago High.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Jerome Foster sounded like a madman on Hitz FM this morning.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Italy will not be at the world cup later this year, thanks to North Macedonia winning the match 1-0.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Why KLAS Sports radio 📻 pop down so often in the West? Every week this station bruk dung.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: She's pushing one under the bus and shielding the other. How hypocritical !

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Some of our politicians and government ministers hate to practice what they preach. They shouldn't wonder why many Jamaicans do not listen to them. Look at the album launch last night. They should be ashamed of themselves.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Three person's are in the pickle yet the hypocrite only point finger at one. When is he going to repent for his sins? Them not biting him?

author: Urnetta Reid
text: I like Yaksta. I've enjoyed his performances, the few times that I have seen him performed. He's a very confident young man. Big up yourself.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Anyhow it wasn't the two who were named in the report, the one not named would be blasting the named one, and maybe ask him to hand in his resignation letter as well. Now they are both blasting the Integrity Commission. Mi like it. Hahaha 😂🤣🤣🤣

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Why am I not surprised? Justice has gone to the dogs 🐶🐕. Jamaica is definitely not a real place. Some people have all the luck in the world 🌎.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Manchester High lost to Jamaica College by one point. One deggeh, deggeh point. I feel your pain.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Shenanigans and lies! Jamaica is not a real place.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Is which ghetto man could a behave suh in court? No wonder, jackass seh the world nuh level.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Some people should never say the word, CORRUPTION. Them must bypass it or shut up them mouth like them have lockjaw.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: What about Calabash at Jakes? Anything happening this year?

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Can you believe it? China will not be joining Russia in the war against Ukraine. In fact China isn't interested in any war and wants it to stop.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Talk truth, if the Opposition leader didn't send the money to the students in the Ukraine, whether his personal money or donations , to help them to get out, the government wouldn't wake up. Them drop the ball on this one, but glad they're helping for free.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Jah know star, the government went loo on the loan thing for the students, who were studying in the Ukraine.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Glad to know that the Jamaican students in the Ukraine, are travelling on a train to Poland. Hope they make it home to Jamaica safely.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Why Jerome Foster cannot be in the studio to co- host the show with Oral Tracey? It's not sounding good when he's not in studio. It doesn't flow. Callers have to call him several times before they hear him. Over to you management.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Minister Kamina Johnson Smith, don't you think it's a little too late now for sympathy. You could more than help the students, to get out of the Ukraine by providing free airfares. Those who are still there are fearful whether they'll make it out alive or not

author: Urnetta Reid
text: It's disgraceful how this government handled the situation with the Jamaican students in the Ukraine.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: We've wasted so much money in this country through corruption, and you mean to tell me, that this government couldn't find the money for the airfare, to help the students studying in the Ukraine to come back home? Shameful ❗

author: Urnetta Reid
text: It was on Facebook that the Mighty Sparrow is dead. That's not true. He's very much alive. Is rumours them spreading. Sorry for the hurt this might have caused Sparrow and his loved ones.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Condolences to the family of the Mighty Sparrow, who died this morning. He had a great life. I'm sure Calypso will be playing wherever he goes in the afterlife.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Announcing that Mr. Carlos Rhoden, the soldier, the Air Jamaica pilot, the politician and former member of parliament,died this morning at his home in St James. May his soul rest in peace.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Many people were looking forward to the drama in court today, but were left disappointed as Judge Sykes adjourned the court.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Minister Johnson Smith, what's happening to the students studying in the Ukraine. Is it true that Russia is about to strike Ukraine?

text: Great going Maggoty High in tonight's  school's challenge match.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: On Stage a gwaan tonight.

text: I feel so sorry 😔😐 for St. Andrew Technical High School. The school challenge team started with zero and ended with zero. What went wrong here?

text: Will Paul Hall continue to coach the Reggae Boys after the qualifiers?

text: It's good to see Andrea Chisholm back on TVJ.

text: Nuh better barrel, nuh better herring. Reggae Boys ship 🚢 sinking.

text: Boris Johnson in hot 🔥 water 💦 this morning. They want him to go.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Tom Brady retired today.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Carey Robinson died last Thursday night in his sleep. Rest in peace. Hill and Gully Ride will not be the same without you. My condolences to your family, friends and loved ones.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Tom Brady has resigned. The greatest ? What say you?

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Who is more intelligent, Orville Higgins or Oral Tracey? One caller said Orville Higgins is more intelligent. What say you?

author: Urnetta Reid
text:
Where's Bobby Reid going
in the Reggae Boys squad? No world 🌎 cup for us.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: I like Craig Butler, but oftentimes he behaves like a spoilt toddler. You should take the blame for this one Craig, and stop pointing fingers.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Benevolent dictator! I love it.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: I would love for somebody to help me with this one. No spectators will be allowed in the national stadium, to watch the upcoming world 🌎 cup qualifiers against the Reggae Boys, yet fans and punters have been at Caymanas Park every racing 🐎 day. How come?

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Bad politics! So said Phillip Paulwell. It only takes one senator from your party for the continuation of the SOE. Why didn't you follow your conviction and get even one of your comrade senators to vote?

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Big, big upset today. Sorry I am not a betting person. I'm sure the coaches of both losing teams, as well as the players, school communities and their supporters are still in shock 😲.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: She was sleeping all along until the orange 🍊 and 🍏 green painting wake her up.

text: The amount of dun know, that I just heard on Hitz 92, boy oh boy.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: Why Bobby keep putting that man on so many boards and everywhere him guh trouble follow him. Is what suh special bout him? He should be kicked off the other boards.

author: Urnetta Reid
text: One hundred million and you're set for life. No envy here, though because I sleep well at nights.
